I'm sorry if I'm trying to bring this thread back from the dead, but there's no evidence that the project has been totally abandoned, and Duke Nukem got released, so... <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br /><br />I made a similar spriteless raycaster in Qbasic/QB64 and I think it would be really cool if this could be made similar. I'd be willing to give source, as long as I got credit. As I said, no sound or sprites are needed, so it just might fly on the NES!<br /><br />Here is a video of my program.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y1qiQRDeEU0">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y1qiQRDeEU0</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4199">castrwilliam</a> — Sun Jul 31, 2011 5:33 pm</p><hr />
